To Create the Rpm : 
/usr/local/bin/fpm -s dir -t rpm -n ${ENV}-webapp -v ${BUILD_NUMBER}.0.0 --prefix=/home/fc-web/www/ --vendor="Freecharge Payment Pvt Ltd" --pacman-user=fc-web --pacman-group=fc-web webapp
 
To Create the Rpm Repo: 
sudo /usr/bin/createrepo --update /var/repo/webapp/prod/

Client side configuration.
- Make sure, it has webserver running. 
- Inside /etc/yum.repos.d/ create a file with name "prod-webapp.repo"
- Contains of the file are - 
[prod-webapp]
name=Prod Webapp Repo
baseurl=http://jenkins-preprod1.sg1.freecharge.com/yum/prod
gpgcheck=0
enabled=1
